post0.title: Open a GitHub Blog in 10 minutes (part 1)
post0.content: Go to the fastpages GitHub repository, click setup instructions | Click ‘on this link’ | Create a repository | . | Wait until the ‘Pull Request’ is done in your repository . | Click Initial setup and follow the directions. Generate SSH key-pair: RSA, 4096 Click to generate secret and deploy keys | Copy ‘Private Key’ and paste it to the secret key (Name: SSH_DEPLOY_KEY) | Copy the ‘Public Key’ and paste it to the deploy key. | . | Click Merge pull request below Initial setup description . | After 2 minutes or so, you can see your blog address at your repository’s README.md |
